# Manual Checklist Maintenance Rule

`dev/test/manual-checklist.md` is the living manual test checklist for X2Chess.
It must reflect every testable user-facing behaviour at all times.

## When to update

Update the checklist **in the same session** as any change that introduces, alters,
or removes something a user can observe or interact with:

| Trigger | Examples |
|---|---|
| New feature | New dialog, new toolbar button, new panel, new import method |
| Changed behaviour | Renamed button, altered workflow, new keyboard shortcut |
| Removed feature | Panel removed, mode dropped, shortcut changed |
| Bug fix that changes observable behaviour | Fix for a crash, silent failure, or wrong result |
| New plan phase completed | Any phase in a `dev/plans/*.plan.md` that ships UI |

Do **not** update for: pure refactoring, type changes, test additions, internal
module splits, or performance work with no visible effect.

## Required actions when updating

1. **Add new items** for every new testable behaviour.
   - Use the section that matches the feature area (LAYOUT, BOARD, ENGINE, etc.).
   - If no section fits, add a new `## SECTION — Name` heading.
2. **Update existing items** if a behaviour changed (do not leave stale descriptions).
3. **Remove items** for features that were deleted entirely.
4. **Update "Last updated" date** at the top to today's date.
5. **Reset any `[x]` to `[ ]`** for items whose behaviour changed — they need re-verification.

## Item format

```
- [ ] **SECTION-N** — One sentence describing exactly what to do and what to expect.
```

- The ID (`SECTION-N`) must be unique across the entire file.
- The description must be concrete enough that the user can reference it by ID
  (e.g. "WEBIMPORT-3 doesn't work") and you will immediately know what it refers to.
- Use imperative or declarative phrasing focused on the observable result:
  *"Paste `https://lichess.org/<id>` opens the full game PGN."*
  Not: *"Test Lichess import."*

## Numbering

- Within each section, number items sequentially: `SECTION-1`, `SECTION-2`, etc.
- When inserting a new item mid-section, append at the end — do not renumber
  existing items (the user may have recorded failures against old IDs).

